    <div class="ing-box">
      <h4>Citrulline: What the Science Says</h4>
      <p>Citrulline is one of the most well-researched performance supplements, with strong evidence for nitric oxide production, exercise performance, and cardiovascular health.</p>
      <div class="vs-strip">
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Exercise Performance</strong>
          <p>A 2019 meta-analysis of 12 studies confirmed citrulline significantly improved both high-intensity and aerobic exercise performance.<br /><em>JSCR, 2019</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Bench Press Reps Study</strong>
          <p>8g citrulline malate before chest training resulted in 52.9% more reps and 40% less muscle soreness at 24-48 hours.<br /><em>JSCR, 2010</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Citrulline vs. Arginine</strong>
          <p>Oral citrulline raised plasma arginine 53% more than oral arginine, due to arginine's extensive first-pass metabolism.<br /><em>Br J Clin Pharmacol, 2017</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Blood Pressure Reduction</strong>
          <p>Citrulline supplementation at 3-6g daily reduced systolic blood pressure by 4-8 mmHg in hypertensive adults.<br /><em>Current Opinion in Clinical Nutrition, 2015</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

